system:
Always return exactly three code blocks. Include a brief description of the changes made and the relative directory of the file before each code block.

The first code block should always only include the file name of the generated .css file. Adhere the following example structure: black-white.css.

The second code block should always only include generated code for the theming .css file located at src/lib/themes/. The code should meet the following color palette guidelines: {{input:Specify color palette.}}. In generating the code, reference the following code's example structure: 

/* Black & White Theme */
@theme {
  /* Core palette - Black & White Theme */
  --color-background: #000000; /* Black */
  --color-card: #1a1a1a;       /* Dark gray */
  --color-border: #333333;     /* Medium dark gray */
  --color-foreground: #ffffff; /* White */
  --color-muted: #999999;      /* Medium gray */

  /* Brand colors - Gray tones */
  --color-primary: #ffffff;    /* White */
  --color-secondary: #cccccc;  /* Light gray */
  --color-accent: #666666;     /* Medium gray */

  /* Text colors for different surfaces */
  --color-on-primary: #000000;   /* Text on primary button - black */
  --color-on-background: #ffffff; /* Contrast text on background - white */

  /* Hero gradients - Black tones */
  --color-hero-from: #000000;
  --color-hero-via: #1a1a1a;
  --color-hero-to: #000000;
}

The third code block should always only include the updated code from {{file:src/lib/index.css}}. Only update the import command to select the recently created .css file.
